// E2E tests for ADR 0105 Phase 3 (BT-2782): the `:recheck image` REPL
// meta-command / `Workspace recheckImage` message-send, and the
// `Behaviour>>precheckCompile:source:` pre-save advisory primitive.
//
// `:recheck image` desugars to `Workspace recheckImage` — the "complete but
// unbounded" whole-image re-check kept out of the automatic per-reload
// trigger (see beamtalk_recheck.erl's moduledoc). `precheckCompile:source:`
// compiles a pending method edit and reports would-be-stale dependents
// *without installing it* — the editor/LSP "check before save" hook.
//
// These cases exercise cross-surface wiring end to end against a real
// running workspace: both ops are reachable, return the documented report
// shape, precheck never installs, and — the whole point of the pre-save
// advisory — a pending signature change genuinely flags a real stale
// dependent (not just an empty default). The precise classification/
// severity/message shape of a finding is covered in more detail by the
// isolated EUnit integration suite (`beamtalk_repl_loader_precheck_tests.erl`,
// `beamtalk_recheck_tests.erl`'s `trigger_pending_*`/`trigger_image_*`
// cases), which controls the ambient class-hierarchy/xref state directly.
//
// IMPORTANT: REPL-protocol cases share one long-lived workspace session
// (see repl_flush_changes_dirty.btscript's note) — class names here are
// unique to this file to avoid collisions with other cases.

// ===========================================================================
// `Workspace recheckImage` — shape of the whole-image report.
// ===========================================================================

Workspace recheckImage isKindOf: Dictionary
// => true

// The report carries checked/stale counts and a findings list.
(Workspace recheckImage) at: #checked
// => _

(Workspace recheckImage) at: #stale
// => _

((Workspace recheckImage) at: #findings) isKindOf: List
// => true

// ===========================================================================
// `:recheck image` — REPL meta-command alias for `Workspace recheckImage`.
// ===========================================================================

:recheck image
// => _

// ===========================================================================
// `precheckCompile:source:` — pre-save advisory: shape of the report, and
// proof that a precheck never installs the pending edit.
// ===========================================================================

Actor subclass: RecheckPrecheckCounter
  size -> Integer => 42
// => RecheckPrecheckCounter

// A dependent whose own return type assumes `size` still answers an
// Integer — the real caller the pre-save advisory should flag once `size`'s
// pending edit changes its return type to String.
Object subclass: RecheckPrecheckDashboard
  refresh: c :: RecheckPrecheckCounter -> Integer => (c size) + 1
// => RecheckPrecheckDashboard

// Sanity: the live behaviour before any precheck.
RecheckPrecheckCounter spawn size
// => 42

// Pending edit: size -> String. Not yet saved — the report is a Dictionary
// shaped like the reload-check report (findings/checked/totalCandidates/
// notChecked/capNote/checkedOwners). A real, type-relevant signature change
// (Integer -> String) against a real dependent (`refresh:`, which assumes
// an Integer) must produce at least one finding — the whole point of the
// pre-save advisory. `findings size > 0` rather than an exact count: this
// file shares one long-lived session with every other REPL-protocol case,
// so the total candidate pool for the common `#size` selector isn't
// controlled the way an isolated EUnit test's is.
(RecheckPrecheckCounter precheckCompile: #size source: "size -> String => 42 printString") isKindOf: Dictionary
// => true

((RecheckPrecheckCounter precheckCompile: #size source: "size -> String => 42 printString") at: #findings) size > 0
// => true

// Never installed: the real message still runs the ORIGINAL method — the
// strongest proof the precheck did not patch the live image.
RecheckPrecheckCounter spawn size
// => 42

// A pending edit with no type-relevant signature change reports an empty
// precheck (`#checked` = 0 — nothing was worth dependent-checking).
((RecheckPrecheckCounter precheckCompile: #size source: "size -> Integer => 43") at: #checked)
// => 0

// Still never installed, after either precheck above.
RecheckPrecheckCounter spawn size
// => 42
